message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.NEURON - The paper proposes a new automatic method for myocardial infarction quantification from LGE-MRI using neural networks and image processing techniques. The paper involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for image segmentation and classification. It also involves medical imaging (cs.MED) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for the application in myocardial infarction detection. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for segmentation and disease detection also falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NEURON).
